Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and finely dice @carrot{3%ounce}(finely diced). Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(diced). Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}(thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #medium ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add carrot and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add onion and a large drizzle of oil; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add mushrooms and @butter{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are just tender, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @autumn spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper to pan with veggies. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} until thoroughly combined, ~{1%minute}.

Sprinkle with @flour{1%tablespoon}; stir to combine. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour @water{1/2%cup} and @beef stock concentrate{1} into pan with beef mixture. Bring to a boil and cook until mixture has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon} until fully incorporated. Taste and season with salt and pepper. If filling is too thick, add a splash of water.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to an 8-by-8-inch baking dish.

Remove @Pillsbury™ Buttermilk Southern Homestyle Biscuits{6%ounce} from package; peel apart each biscuit at the center to create two thinner ones.

Top filling evenly with biscuits.

> TIP: For an extra-rich experience, place 1 TBSP butter in a small microwave-safe bowl; microwave until melted, about 30 seconds. Brush tops of biscuits with melted butter.

Bake on top rack until biscuits are golden brown, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Let pot pie cool at least ~{5%minutes}. Spoon into shallow bowls or plates and serve.